# 🚗 Swite-Ride Project Documentation

---

# 📌 Overview

Swite-Ride is a scalable, real-time ride-hailing backend system built using **NestJS (Node.js framework)**. Unlike traditional ride-hailing platforms, Swite-Ride introduces a **bidding-based ride allocation system**, where drivers compete by submitting bids for ride requests, and riders select the most suitable offer based on price, ETA, or preference.

The system is designed with production-level architecture principles including modular design, real-time communication, caching strategies, and background processing.

---

# 🎯 Objectives

* Build a real-time ride-hailing platform
* Implement a bidding-based ride selection mechanism
* Ensure high scalability and maintainability
* Support live tracking and real-time communication
* Provide a clean modular architecture ready for microservices migration

---

# 🧠 System Architecture

Swite-Ride follows a **Modular Monolith Architecture** using NestJS.

### Key Principles:

* Each business domain is isolated in its own module
* Shared logic is extracted into core and shared layers
* Real-time communication is handled via WebSockets (Socket.IO)
* Performance optimization is achieved using Redis caching

