# 🚀 End-to-End System Workflow

## 1. Application Entry

* User opens the application
* Authentication check (JWT validation)
* Role detection (Rider / Driver)

---

## 2. Authentication Flow

* User registers or logs in
* JWT token is generated
* Token is stored on client side
* Protected routes require token validation

---

## 3. Rider Ride Creation Flow

* Rider selects pickup and destination
* System calculates estimated route (OSRM integration via cron/utility)
* Ride request is created with status: `PENDING`
* System broadcasts ride request to available drivers via Socket.IO

---

## 4. Driver Discovery Flow

* Drivers receive real-time ride request
* Drivers evaluate request (distance, demand, availability)
* Each driver submits a bid including:

  * Price
  * ETA

---

## 5. Bidding Phase

* All bids are stored in database and optionally cached in Redis
* Rider receives live bid updates via WebSocket
* Rider can compare bids in real-time

---

## 6. Ride Selection

* Rider selects a preferred bid
* System assigns selected driver to ride
* Ride status changes to `ACCEPTED`
* Other bids are rejected automatically

---

## 7. Ride Execution

* Driver starts the ride
* Ride status changes to `IN_PROGRESS`
* Live GPS tracking begins
* Driver location is continuously streamed via Socket.IO

---

## 8. Live Tracking

* Rider sees real-time driver movement on map
* Location updates are throttled for performance optimization

---

## 9. Ride Completion

* Driver ends the ride
* System updates status to `COMPLETED`
* Payment process is triggered
* Ride data is stored in history

---

## 10. Post-Ride Flow

* Rider rates driver
* Driver rating is updated
* Transaction is stored in payments module
* Analytics data is updated (optional)

